-- AIG profit rises 12.5 pct
-- 
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 04:05PM EDT
-- None



Aug 4 (Reuters) - American International Group Inc <AIG.N> reported a 12.5 percent rise in quarterly profit, helped by strong performance across all its key businesses.

Net income attributable to AIG rose to $3.07 billion, or $2.10 per share, in the second quarter ended June 30 from $2.73 billion, or $1.84 per share, a year earlier. The U.S. insurer's net income for the quarter included a $1.4 billion after-tax gain on the sale of ILFC.